Eve Addison developed a strange swelling in her collarbone whenever she drank gin and tonic . 
  She assumed she must have an allergy - but when switching brands failed to help she developed night sweats and a rash  . 
  Tests revealed she was suffering Hodgkin Lymphoma - cancer of the lymphatic system . 
  Most common symptom is painless swellings in the neck, armpit or groin . 
  Miss Addison underwent six months of chemotherapy and has now been given the all clear . 
 